    "However, despite the numerous benefits associated with ChatGPT, a study conducted by Day (2023) suggests that its use in research may have adverse consequences for students' academic success.",
    "Day argues that ChatGPT-generated results may include fake citations, references, and artifact answers, posing potential risks to the credibility of academic work.",
    "Furthermore, the presence of ChatGPT in the higher education sector introduces concerns about academic misconduct.",
    "According to Dehouche (2021), students may leverage ChatGPT to delegate tasks such as assignment writing and research, thereby potentially compromising the integrity of their academic responsibilities.",
